  "Border",
  "Follow signs to UK Border. e-Gates open to most passports incl. GCC. Have your accommodation address ready.",
  "SIM / eSIM",
  "Activate your eSIM on airport Wi-Fi. Or buy an EE / Three SIM from the arrivals shop (£10 gets you 20GB).",
  "Cash",
  "Take £50–£100 from an ATM (Halifax / HSBC — never the Travelex booth). Cards work everywhere but keep a note.",
  "Train, not taxi",
  "Elizabeth Line from LHR T2/T3/T5 to central London: 30 min, £11.50. From LGW take the Gatwick Express: 30 min, £22.",
  "Oyster / Contactless",
  "Tap your bank card at the gates. It caps at £8.90/day automatically. No Oyster needed for most travellers.",
  "Hotel",
  "Check-in is usually from 15:00. Most luxury hotels will hold luggage from 09:00 so you can start exploring.",
  "First meal",
  "Head to Borough Market (Southwark) or Dishoom (Covent Garden). Recover with tea, then a nap. Jet lag rewards discipline.",
